 Urges Supreme Court to redeem judiciary’s image A political activist and former Deputy National Publicity Secretary of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Timi Frank, has called on the international community to place visa restrictions on the five justices of the Appeal Court that presided over the Presidential Election Petition Tribunal (PEPT) over gross miscarriage of justice and flagrant breach of the Constitution. Frank also called on the National Judicial Council (NJC) and the Supreme to review the tribunal’s ruling and sanction the Justices for deliberate perversion of justice. Continue reading Timi Frank seeks visa ban against PEPT Justices at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard ABUJA – Comrade Timi Frank, political activist and former Deputy National Publicity Secretary of the All Progressives Congress (APC), has blamed corrupt elements in Nigeria’s judiciary for most of the country’s problems. As a result, he has invited the international community, especially the United States of America, to beam their searchlight… August 9, 2019 In "News" Demands urgent stop to killings Seeks compensation for victims To visit Julius Malema Calls on AU to Intervene A political activist and former Deputy National Publicity Secretary of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Timi Frank, has called on the President of South Africa, Cyril Ramaphosa, to urgently halt attacks… September 4, 2019 In "News" <p class=""><strong>Timi Frank had condemned Buhari's suspension of Onnoghen as the CJN.</strong></p> <p class=""><strong>Former Deputy National Publicity Secretary of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Timi Frank, has called on the international community to urgently prevail on President Muhammadu Buhari to reverse "illegal" suspension of the Chief Justice of Nigeria (CJN),… January 26, 2019 In "News"